The Office of the First Lady has announced that Melania Trump will participate in the 2019 International Women of Courage Celebration on March 7, 2019, as part of Women's History Month. Melania Trump has presented the International Women of Courage Award for the past three years and will return to the State Department to give remarks and present the award to a group of remarkable women. The IWOC Award has honored over 120 women from more than 65 different countries over the last 13 years. This event is open to the press, and interested outlets should apply through the State Department.